A lightweight GTK3-based real-time system monitoring application specifically designed for Raspberry Pi.

System Analyser provides comprehensive system metrics monitoring with a clean, native interface. It displays CPU usage, temperature, memory, and other vital system statistics in real-time, perfect for keeping an eye on your Raspberry Pi's performance.

Key Features:
• Real-time CPU usage and temperature monitoring
• Memory and swap usage tracking
• System uptime and load average display
• CPU clock speed and voltage monitoring
• Data logging to CSV files for analysis
• Native GTK3 interface that integrates with your desktop
• Lightweight and efficient resource usage

Perfect for:
• Monitoring system performance during heavy tasks
• Tracking temperature to prevent thermal throttling
• Analyzing system behavior over time with CSV logs
• Learning about system resource management
• Keeping tabs on your Pi's health

How to Use:
After installation, launch "System Analyser" from your application menu under System or Monitor categories. The main window will display real-time metrics. Data is automatically logged to ~/.local/share/system-analyser/system_metrics.csv for later analysis.

The application is optimized for all Raspberry Pi models and works on both 32-bit (armhf) and 64-bit (arm64) systems.

Website: https://github.com/bathiatuss/system_analyser
Support: https://github.com/bathiatuss/system_analyser/issues
